# Æther — Supabase + Vercel Environment Variables

Copy this file to `.env` and fill in your Supabase project credentials.

```bash
cp .env.example .env
```

## Local Development

Start the Supabase local stack:

```bash
supabase start
```

This will print your local `SUPABASE_URL` and `SUPABASE_ANON_KEY`. Use those below.

## Production (Vercel)

Set these in your Vercel project dashboard:
https://vercel.com/your-account/brand-aether/settings/environment-variables

---

# Your Supabase project URL (e.g., https://abc123.supabase.co)
VITE_SUPABASE_URL=

# Your Supabase anon/public key
VITE_SUPABASE_ANON_KEY=
